</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ieuan ap Gruffudd was born about 1400, in Llwyn-Dafydd, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Iorwerth ap David, was 52 and his mother, Tibot or Mrs Iorwerth Ap Dafydd Llwyd, was 72."},"et":{"ABT    1400–":"umbes 1400–Surnud","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1430–Female":"1430–Surnud","–1435":"–1435","–1501":"–1501","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","ABT    1400":"umbes 1400","1501":"1501","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1430":"1430","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","of Llwyn Dafydd,Llandysiliogogo,Cardiganshire,Wales":"Llwyn-Dafydd, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT    1400–":"noin 1400–Kuollut","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1430–Female":"1430–Kuollut","–1435":"–1435","–1501":"–1501","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","ABT    1400":"noin 1400","1501":"1501","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1430":"1430","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Llwyn Dafydd,Llandysiliogogo,Cardiganshire,Wales":"Llwyn-Dafydd, Cardiganshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT    1400–":"environ 1400–Décédé","1400–Male":"1400–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1430–Female":"1430–Décédée","–1435":"–1435","–1501":"–1501","1350–Male":"1350–Décédé","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","ABT    1400":"environ 1400","1501":"1501","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1430":"1430","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","Wales, United Kingdom":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","of Llwyn Dafydd,Llandysiliogogo,Cardiganshire,Wales":"Llwy